The paper deals with optimization problems in dynamic flow networks, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of finding optimal sink locations for flow evacuation can also be seen as a network optimization problem (cs.NE). The use of regret optimization is a common technique in game theory and decision making (cs.GT), and the paper also involves the development of algorithms (cs.DM) and the analysis of computational complexity (cs.CC).
